<module>
    <h>briagha</h>
    <p><g>briagha</g>
        <en>beautiful</en> is a <a href="?xx=adjectives/simple_adjectives">simple adjective</a>.</p>
    <p>Note that <g>briagha</g> can also be spelled as <g>brèagha</g>, especially in recent
        writings.</p>

    <section>
        <h>nouns</h>
        <module id="latha_briagha">
            <h>latha briagha</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=latha">latha</a> briagha</g>
                <en>a beautiful day</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha latha briagha blàth ann.</gd>
                        <tr>It is a beautiful warm day.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [228] [adapted]</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Bha latha briagha ann agus bha a’ ghrian a’ deàrrsadh.</gd>
                        <tr>It was a beautiful day and the sun was shining.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 21</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </module>
    </section>






